<F P=106> [Report from "El Salvador Telepress" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Costa Rican President-elect Jose Maria Figueres 
visited our country for three hours and met with President 
Alfredo Cristiani. Mr. Jose Maria Figueres said that in this 
country the Central American integration processs is considered 
truly necessary for regional development. He arrived in our 
country to meet with President Alfredo Cristiani following a 
15-hour visit to Honduras. Upon his arrival, Mr. Figueres was 
welcomed by the leader at the presidential residence, where they 
met behind closed doors. 
  Accompanied by Foreign Minister-designate Fernando Naranjo 
and Economics Minister-designate Marcos Vargas, the future Costa 
Rican president and President Cristiani discussed the marketing 
of coffee and bananas, two products extremely important for the 
region. They also viewed their countries' possible entry into 
NAFTA, signed by Mexico, the United States, and Canada. Mr. 
Figueres also invited President Cristiani to visit Costa Rica on 
8 May for his presidential inauguration. After his three-hour 
visit to El Salvador, Figueres left for Guatemala, where he is 
scheduled to meet with Guatemalan President Ramiro de Leon 
Carpio. He plans to end his tour in Guatemala. 

